<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2344] PostingsConsumer#merge does not call finishDoc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2344</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;We discovered that the current merge function in PostingsConsumer is not calling the #finishDoc method. This does not have consequences for the standard codec (since the lastPosition is set to 0 in #startDoc, and its #finishDoc method is empty), but for the SepCodec, this results in position file corruption (the lastPosition is set to 0 in #finishDoc for the SepCodec).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
